== Server requirements ==
* Apache or other webserver
* PHP
* MySQL
* A static IP

== Setup on server ==
* Clone git repo.
* Set up webserver to find the files.
* Create db and users.

== Setup on phone ==
* Install BigBrotherGPS.apk (app)
* Set up server URL
* Secret is used as device name

== Security ==
* SSL is not required, but should be used.

== Alternative android client ==
* http://osmand.net/ can also be used as client. To do this activate the plugin for "logging services", and go to settings for this plugin. Under "online tracking" set web adress to http(s)://servername/?latitude={0}&longitude={1}&timestamp={2}&hdop={3}&altitude={4}&speed={5}&secret=<name of your device>